item.description: Peer to Peer skill session with a focus on paddling strokes including bracing, edging turning as well as forward and reverse paddling techniques. This is a PARTICIPATORY event. NO SPECTATORS! If you come, dress to possibly be in the water! (the water is still quite warm) The air temperature may be cooler so dress appropriately and bring extra clothing. This is an opportunity to learn & practice paddling techniques that will improve your kayak propulsion and maneuvering skills. Equipment Required: PFD, paddle, pump, paddle float, lunch/snacks, plenty of water or other hydration beverages. We'll Launch at noon from Neal's Cove Boat Launch and return to Launch area Approx: 3:00 p.m. possibly later. All kayak types are welcome as well as all paddle types including touring, high angle, wing or greenland style. You will lear how to best utilize your particular paddle type with your kayak as well as try other types if you care to.
item.name: Skills Session - Kayak paddling strokes practice, bracing, edging, turning etc.
